b600			; | TABLE ( s .. sx c -- a) For the number c of strings s on the stack. Generate a look up table array a | DONE 
b600			; | | Takes a list of strings and creates a block of pointers to each string which can then be used 
b600			; | | in any kind of lookup or iteration.  
